 This install applies to "Desert Strike - Return to the Gulf" © 1993 Electronic Arts

 This install requires WHDLoad and DIC to be in the path. Both can be found in
 the WHDLoad package.
 To install from a different drive than DF0: select installation mode Expert.

 The installed program requires 1.0 MB ChipMem and 1.5 MB OtherMem.
 It can be quit by pressing num '*' (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").

 If you have problems with this installation please try and get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, NOVBRMOVE, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also fails, please inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad WWW-Page or create a mantis issue directly
 at http://mantis.whdload.de

 For the full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
	http://www.whdload.de/
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/

 Features:
 ---------
 - System friendly disk imager.
 - Custom1=1 - Trainers - Infinite Power, Fuel, Hellfire, Hydra, and Cannon
 - Custom2=X - Level Select
 - Custom3=1 - Disable Blitter patches
 - Custom4=1 - Enable alternate CD32 joypad controls
	Red			- Always fires the Cannon
	Blue		- Always fires Hydra
	Green		- Always Fires Hellfire
 - Custom5=1 - Skip Intro
 - Supports two versions
 
 If CD32 pad is detected, the controls below are enabled no matter what:
 
	Yellow/Play 			- Bring Up Map Screen/Exit Map screen
	Play+Forward+Reverse 	- Quit
	Green+Forward+Reverse 	- Abort Game

 With a third button joystick:
 
     second button          - switches weapons
	 third button 			- Bring Up Map Screen/Exit Map screen
	 
 If CUSTOM4 is not set, the controls stick to "classic" with extras:
 
    Blue / Forward: changes weapon (original game only used blue/2nd button)
 
 History:
 --------
 
 Version 3.2 (09.january.2022) by JOTD:
 - support for 3-joystick button. Third button brings map (F10) (issue #0005348)
 - fixed potential sound issues (CPU dependent loops)
 - removed BUTTONWAIT to force NTSC. Use NTSC tooltype
 
 Version 3.1 (12.may.2019) by Keith Krellwitz/Abaddon & JOTD:
 - Removed division by 0 at the end of the intro (no need for novbrmove tooltype)
 - added automatic joypad detection
 - CUSTOM4 now allows alternate CD32 controls, but with classic controls (no CUSTOM4)
   status screen/abort mission/quit to OS joypad controls are active
 - joystick left/right select mission password in "enter password" menu:
   that plus joypad controls means no need for keyboard anymore for the entire game
 - music cpu active loops fixed
 - Fixed issue with copperlist being corrupted when restarting level (because of previous copper fix)
 
 Version 3.0 (13.mar.2016) by Keith Krellwitz/Abaddon:
 - Removed all JST specific code and converted to use patchlists
 - Added Level Select 
 - Added Trainer - Infinite Power, Fuel, Hellfire, Hydra, and Cannon
 - Blitter Waits Added
 - Removed 6x Disk Access
 - Fixed issue with copperlist being set before the its loaded 
   (after main menu, press fire to skip intro, mission briefing, etc.)
 - Reworked the CD32 controls as requested
	Red 	- Always fires the Cannon
	Blue	- Always fires Hydra
	Green	- Always Fires Hellfire
	(The weapon select no longer functions)
 - Added Button Wait to force NTSC
 - Second version supported
 - Custom5=1 - Skip Intro - Jumps to the Main Menu
 - Not Publicly Released
  
 Version 2.3 (21.jan.2013) by Keith Krellwitz/Abaddon:
 - Custom4=1 - Enable CD32 joypad support
 	Red 			- Fire
	Yellow 			- Bring Up Map Screen/Exit Map screen
 	Play 			- Pause 
 	Play+Forward+Reverse 	- Quit
 	Green+Forward+Reverse 	- Abort Game
  
 Version 2.2 (07.july.2007) by JOTD:
 - no need for NOVBRMOVE anymore
 - reworked install & icons
 - source code included

 previous versions done by JOTD (1996-2007, no history available)
 - Rewrote memory allocation so the loader now only needs 512K chip/512K 24bit RAM
 - Removed routines that lit the floppy led (I hate that floppy led :) )
 - Second button changes weapons (VERY useful during intensive fights)
 - Fast decrunch using relocated routines in fastmem
 - Manual included


 Cheat:

 Enter "HARDCASE" to get unlimited weapons, but low armour.
 Enter "PSYCHOTI"? (This is only active in one of the versions)

 LEVEL 2-"BQJRAEF"
 LEVEL 3-"KLJLTOE"
 LEVEL 4-"WEIVVJT"
 END SEQUENCE-"ONKKQKF"
 
 10 GUYS AND INFINITE AMMO-"BQQQAEZ"

